Here's your exact pipeline converted to use shared library:

Step 1 — Create Shared Library Repo

jenkins-shared-library/
      ├── vars/
      │     ├── checkoutCode.groovy
      │     ├── buildMaven.groovy
      │     ├── dockerBuild.groovy
      │     ├── dockerPush.groovy
      │     └── deployToK8s.groovy

Step 2 — Write Shared Library Functions

// vars/checkoutCode.groovy
def call(String repoUrl) {
    git repoUrl
    echo "✅ Code checked out from ${repoUrl}"
}

// vars/buildMaven.groovy
def call() {
    sh 'mvn clean package'
    echo "✅ Maven build done"
}

// vars/dockerBuild.groovy
def call(String imageName, String tag) {
    sh "docker build -t ${imageName}:${tag} ."
    echo "✅ Docker image built: ${imageName}:${tag}"
}

// vars/dockerPush.groovy
def call(String imageName, String tag) {
    sh "docker push ${imageName}:${tag}"
    echo "✅ Docker image pushed: ${imageName}:${tag}"
}

// vars/deployToK8s.groovy
def call(String manifest) {
    sh "kubectl apply -f ${manifest}"
    echo "✅ Deployed to Kubernetes"
}

Step 3 — Your Jenkinsfile 

After — With Shared Library ✅

@Library('jenkins-shared-lib@main') _    // import shared library

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {

        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                checkoutCode('https://github.com/example/app.git')  // ← shared function
            }
        }

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                buildMaven()                                          // ← shared function
            }
        }

        stage('Docker Build') {
            steps {
                dockerBuild('myapp', "${BUILD_NUMBER}")               // ← shared function
            }
        }

        stage('Push Image') {
            steps {
                dockerPush('myapp', "${BUILD_NUMBER}")                // ← shared function
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy to K8s') {
            steps {
                deployToK8s('deployment.yaml')                        // ← shared function
            }
        }
    }
}

What Changed

Before:                          After:
─────────────────────────        ─────────────────────────
sh 'mvn clean package'    →      buildMaven()
sh 'docker build ...'     →      dockerBuild('myapp', tag)
sh 'docker push ...'      →      dockerPush('myapp', tag)
kubectl apply ...         →      deployToK8s('deployment.yaml')

All logic lives in         →     Jenkinsfile is clean
